<br>
I've been hearing of enchanter NPCs mezzing parties and charming the MT to attack other party members.  Wizard NPCs casting IC and 750 point AoE rain spells, breaking mezzes.<br>
<br>
Of course, they still hit like warriors and have the HP/Mitigation of warriors, are still harder to resist then an NPC would be and harder to interrupt then an NPC would be.<br>
<br>
If so, it seems that it was a huge nerf to the player base. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeka>Aeka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 1423<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/6/02 9:52:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=366.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Caster AI changes</span><hr size=1> I've heard the same thing too...  Of course I won't exactly believe it till I see it. ^_^<br>
<br>
If this is true I don't think it is that bad.  Not only does it change the same humdrum exp encounter but it makes Paladins and Enchanters more valuable for spell surpression.<br>
<br>
When you have a strong group it is better to overwhelm the monster and let it cast its whimpy spells against you instead of trying to surpress them.  The &quot;group exp saving&quot; of using a stun to stop a 200 point nuke isn't that compelling.  However if the monster's behavior changed to where they are casting much stronger and much more dangerous stuff it suddenly makes spell supression important.  If you see a monster that you know that can cast charm then you better pull out a bunch of stuns to stop help stop it.<br>
<br>
However we need to be wary of them making it too strong.  A player charm from an NPC shouldn't last a minute.  There needs to be a penalty for not being able to stop a monster from doing their spell but not something that will break the group every time.<br>
<br>
ps. don't you hate it when you hit &quot;post&quot; too soon? ^_^ <p><font size="+1">
