<br>
You have no idea what it is to &quot;have it hard&quot; - so dont preach to me about how tough these caster changes are. <p><a href=http://www.fallenalliance.org/scripts/members/profile.pl?who=Memnenth>Sir Memnenth Peredhil</a><br>Guildleader - <a href=http://www.fallenalliance.org>Fallen Alliance</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 396<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/6/02 12:08:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=366.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Funny</span><hr size=1> I understand that people with a long grind ahead to level 60 want things to be as easy as possible.  I understand that any change that seems to make things harder will not be welcomed by that crowd.<br>
<br>
I personally feel differently though, because I think over time the low level game overall has gotten too easy.  Yes I'm level 60 so you could argue it's easy for me to say that.  But even I had a lot of advantages over people who leveled up before me.  Big advantages.  The 40% hybrid exp penalty was removed when I still had many, many levels to go.  I had a lot of Skyshrine armor at level 55.  Even the rounds of melee class balancing, which increased Paladin's power dramatically, was done while I still had many levels to go.<br>
<br>
This isn't unique to Paladins either.  Just about every class has gotten significantly upgraded over time, to the point where soloing is often the best exp, and most exp areas with full groups are trivial to the point of boredom.<br>
<br>
Now that casters are getting their own round of upgrades, it will make things even more trivial--and probably more boring.  If the game becomes so easy that everything is trivial, nothing is challenging anymore, people will get bored with it.<br>
<br>
I think it is a smart thing to keep the difficulty of encounters in line with player abilities.  Doing it by improving the AI, rather than just increasing stats like damage and HPs is better IMO because it makes things more interesting rather than just longer/more difficult.<br>
<br>
I also agree with the poster who says it will be good for Paladins.  We are the first class to be put on Stun duty, and are the best suited for the role.  Making that a more valuable skill will make Paladins more desirable, without even having to make us more powerful in any way.  In the same way that Paladins were sought out as tanks in the new CT when taunt didn't work, Paladins will be sought out for groups in caster heavy camps if it now makes a big difference to be able to stop them.<br>
<br>
IMO trivial encounters = boring = players losing interest in the game.  The most fun I've had playing EQ were the really tough encounters, the ones where I didn't know if I'd make it out alive.  I'd rather have casters who keep my on my toes than a camp that is so boring and repetitive that the biggest challenge is not falling asleep.<br>
<br>
I do hope the changes they make work properly though.  I exped in Sirens Grotto for a while (enchanter mobs who charm), and one time some charms got through.  I was charmed for a bit, but after it wore off I was unable to hit the mob at all.  I was swinging away (not sure if I was getting miss messages since I have those turned off), but absolutely nothing was landing.  As soon as my druid and enchanter died, I could suddenly hit the mob again.  It was some sort of bug but my threesome died because of it, if I was able to melee I would have prevailed.  <br>
<br>
I hope these new changes, especially ones like charm and mez that do weird things that might not be all that well tested, don't cause too many problems due to bugs.<br>
<br>
I do understand why people who have a ways to go don't want things to get harder, but I'd encourage you to think about how much easier it has gotten as well.   <p><BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a>
